children.label: What is the status of your supply chain strategy?

children.name: Cooperation
children.label: To what extent do the various departments in the Supply Chain cooperate and use the same systems?
Integrated Systems
children.description: The departments, customers and suppliers have access to a completely integrated computer system, with standard definitions. Consistent reporting and analytics are freely available to anyone who needs them

children.label: Cooperation is the norm
children.description: Cooperation between both internal and external departments and partners is the norm. Computer systems are integrated across the Supply Chain and are centrally administered

children.label: Departmental Cooperation
children.description: Departmental cooperation is increasing, particularly with departments that depend on each others work. The departmental systems are being replaced by integrated systems that work across departments

children.label: Some Cooperation
children.description: There is some cooperation between departments and most of the systems within the departments have been automated, although different departments often use different systems

children.label: Autonomus
children.description: The departments are mostly autonomus, mostly using manual systems which are differ from department to department

children.name: Move_data
children.label:
How does the supply chain data move 
across nodes in the organization?
All definitions are stored centrally
children.description: All data definitions, metadata and governance rules are stored and maintained centrally and are applied to all transactions in the supply chain (both internal and external)

children.label: Data flow is completely automated
children.description: Data flows are completely automated using an integrated platform which includes a common data model and integrated meta data definitions

children.label: Data flow is automated
children.description:
Data flow across nodes is mainly automated using electronic data interchange (EDI),
 ETL applications and interfacing and possibly cloud-based platforms

children.label: Some automated data integration
children.description:
There is some automated data integration between both internal and external systems. 
Management can follow the process using spreadsheets and basic reporting

children.label: Fax and Email
children.description: Manually  data is transferred on paper using fax and/or email and telephone

children.name: Integrated_sc
children.label:
To what extent is the Supply Chain a set of integrated processes 
instead of a number of disjointed functions?
Each node has its own systems
children.description:
Each node has its own separate systems which try to be compliant with local regulations,
reporting is transactional rather than analytical

children.label: Processes are being defined
children.description:
Processes are being defined and some have been automated typically 
Inventory management or demand forecasting

children.label: Processes in the Supply Chain have been analysed
children.description:
The supply chain has been analysed and defined as a set of unified processes, 
increasingly technology is being used for real-time process monitoring

children.label: Unification of processes is complete
children.description:
Unification of supply chain processes has been completed; 
analysis is allowing innovation in process improvement to be adopted

children.label: Processes are agile and responsive
children.description:
Processes are agile and responsive creating value for customers and 
stakeholders through supply chain excellence
